9 An Act relating to courts; amending 20 O.S. 2021,
Section 1651.1, which relates to professional and
10 educational programs for judges; authorizing
professional and education programs provided by the
11 Council on Judicial Complaints to satisfy mandatory
judicial continuing legal education requirements; and
12 providing an effective date.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 20 O.S. 2021, Section 1651.1, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 Section 1651.1. A. The Council on Judicial Complaints is
19 authorized to provide funding for the attendance and participation
20 of state, municipal, and administrative judges in professional and
21 educational programs, schools, or conferences for the purpose of
22 improving the quality of the Oklahoma Judiciary and to improve the
23 administration of justice in this state. The Council may contract
24 or partner with public or private entities or otherwise fund and
Req. No. 16052 Page 1

1 part icipate in the development, implementation, and conduct of
2 professional and educational programs for judges.
3 B. Professional and education programs, schools, or conferences
4 provided by the Council on Judicial Complaints as authorized by
5 subsection A of this section shall satisfy mandatory judicial
6 continuing legal education requirements without additional approval.
7 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
